
IF you're in the market for some of the most expensive houses in Scotland - then here is the pick of the bunch.
In Edinburgh you can go for the very top of the market with a &pound;2.5million priced Castle Gogar which has seven bedrooms and five reception rooms, as well as a gym, gamesroom and stables.
In Glasgow, the top of the market is the impressive Veneto Villa which is on the market for offers over &pound;1.65million and that would get you a five bedrooms and your very own cinema for your money.
You can have a look at them in more detail at www.savills.co.uk.


